{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"imminent-reformable-fruitbat","description":"## Context\nFor high assurance, a developer routes the gate to a trusted rebar-mcp server that runs the verifier and signs. Integrity requires the server to fetch authoritative state itself (never client inputs). Includes the AWS deployment.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The trusted rebar-mcp path fetches ticket state + code-at-commit from authoritative remotes itself and runs the gate on that; a test asserts a client-supplied doctored input does NOT change the signed verdict.\n- [ ] The AWS MCP-server infra declares human/admin authentication for its endpoint, least-privilege IAM for the signing key + repo read, and stores the signing key in a secrets manager/KMS.\n- [ ] The default local path stays offline and never wedges an op (test/asserted).","id":"ee0b-c5e2-3454-42f1","parent_id":"6d0d-7580-e18f-48c3","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"op-cert: trusted rebar-mcp remote-execution path (authoritative-state fetch) + AWS infra"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783735897033195001,"uuid":"a6f7ccc9-595d-4b88-8298-58e666a94ed5"}